import "./explore.css";
import "./userSearch.css";
```

But `interestSections.css` is imported inside `InterestSections.jsx` itself:
```js
import "./interestSections.css";
```

This is fine — the CSS is co-located with the component that uses it, so it will be bundled when `InterestSections` is imported. This is **not a bug**. No action needed; noting it for completeness.

